rus Variants to Spread use?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"It primarily maps to binary search and segment tree, within the broader topic of geometry.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Is Minimum Time For K Virus Variants to Spread good for interviews?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Yes — as a Hard problem it is a solid practice target. Pair it with related problems in the same pattern family for spaced repetition.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Where can I read the official statement?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Open the official LeetCode page for constraints and examples: https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-time-for-k-virus-variants-to-spread/\\\"}}]}\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"14:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"container-af py-8\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"script\\\",null,{\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/ld+json\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"@context\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://schema.org\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Article\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"headline\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Minimum Time For K Virus Variants to Spread\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"description\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Original Hard explanation for Minimum Time For K Virus Variants to Spread (LeetCode #1956). Pattern: binary search. Time O(nlogn * logr), space O(n). Multi-language solutions and interview tips.\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"url\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/minimum-time-for-k-virus-variants-to-spread\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"author\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Organization\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"AlgoForge\\\\\\\"},\\\\\\\"publisher\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Organization\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"AlgoForge\\\\\\\"},\\\\\\\"datePublished\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"2026-01-01\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"dateModified\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"2026-07-17\\\\\\\"}\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"script\\\",null,{\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/ld+json\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"$1d\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"script\\\",null,{\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/ld+json\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"@context\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://schema.org\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowTo\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"How to solve Minimum Time For K Virus Variants to Spread\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"description\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Original Hard explanation for Minimum Time For K Virus Variants to Spread (LeetCode #1956). Pattern: binary search. Time O(nlogn * logr), space O(n). Multi-language solutions and interview tips.\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"step\\\\\\\":[{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowToStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":1,\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Read the official problem statement on LeetCode\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowToStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":2,\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Solve on paper / whiteboard first\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowToStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":3,\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Implement the binary search and segment tree approach\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowToStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":4,\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Verify edge cases from the checklist\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowToStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":5,\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"State time and space complexity aloud\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowToStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":6,\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Compare with the AlgoForge reference solution\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowToStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":7,\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Schedule a revision session\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"nav\\\",null,{\\\"aria-label\\\":\\\"Breadcrumb\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm text-muted-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"script\\\",null,{\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/ld+json\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"@context\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://schema.org\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"itemListElement\\\\\\\":[{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"ListItem\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":1,\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Home\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://algoforge.dev/\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"ListItem\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":2,\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Problems\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"ListItem\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":3,\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Minimum Time For K Virus Variants to Spread\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/minimum-time-for-k-virus-variants-to-spread\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}}],\\\"$L1e\\\"]}],\\\"$L1f\\\"]}]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"20:I[56303,[\\\"/_next/static/chunks/2fvm6eoqeukxu.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/1ntn7efqc-iiw.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0plpm2axnqe9k.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/259rkrk9l2f9c.js\\\"],\\\"BookmarkButton\\\"]\\n21:I[705747,[\\\"/_next/static/chunks/2fvm6eoqeukxu.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/1ntn7efqc-iiw.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0plpm2axnqe9k.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/259rkrk9l2f9c.js\\\"],\\\"CodeTabs\\\"]\\n1e:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"ol\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-1.5\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"li\\\",\\\"/\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-1.5\\\",\\\"children\\\":[false,[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Home\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"li\\\",\\\"/problems\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-1.5\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"aria-hidden\\\":true,\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-border\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"/\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/problems\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Problems\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"li\\\",\\\"/problems/minimum-time-for-k-virus-variants-to-spread\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-1.5\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"aria-hidden\\\":true,\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-border\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"/\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-foreground font-medium\\\",\\\"aria-current\\\":\\\"page\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Minimum Time For K Virus Variants to Spread\\\"}]]}]]}]\\n22:T1b60,\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"// Time:  O(nlogn * logr), r is the sum of range x size and range y size\\n// Space: O(n)\\n\\n// competitive programming solution\\nclass Solution {\\npublic:\\n    int minDayskVariants(vector\\u003cvector\\u003cint\\u003e\\u003e\\u0026 points, int k) {\\n        std::transform(begin(points), end(points), begin(points),\\n                       [](const auto\\u0026 v) {\\n                           return vector\\u003cint\\u003e({v[0] + v[1], v[0] - v[1]});  // rotate\\n                       });\\n        const auto\\u0026 compare_y = [](const vector\\u003cint\\u003e\\u0026 a, const vector\\u003cint\\u003e\\u0026 b) { return a[1] \\u003c b[1]; };\\n        const int min_x = (*min_element(cbegin(points), cend(points)))[0];\\n        const int max_x = (*max_element(cbegin(points), cend(points)))[0];\\n        const int min_y = (*min_element(cbegin(points), cend(points), compare_y))[1];\\n        const int max_y = (*max_element(cbegin(points), cend(points), compare_y))[1];\\n        int64_t left = 0, right = ((int64_t(max_x) - min_x) + (int64_t(max_y) - min_y) + 1) / 2;\\n        while (left \\u003c= right) {\\n            const auto\\u0026 mid = left + (right - left) / 2;\\n            if (check(points, k, mid)) {\\n                right = mid - 1;\\n            } else {\\n                left = mid + 1;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return left;                       \\n    }\\n\\nprivate:\\n    class SegmentTree {\\n    public:\\n        SegmentTree(int N)\\n            : N_(N),\\n              tree_(2 * N),\\n              lazy_(N)\\n        {\\n            H_ = 1;\\n            while ((1 \\u003c\\u003c H_) \\u003c N) {\\n                ++H_;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        void update(int L, int R, int h) {\\n            L += N_; R += N_;\\n            int L0 = L, R0 = R;\\n            while (L \\u003c= R) {\\n                if ((L \\u0026 1) == 1) {\\n                    apply(L++, h);\\n                }\\n                if ((R \\u0026 1) == 0) {\\n                    apply(R--, h);\\n                }\\n                L \\u003e\\u003e= 1; R \\u003e\\u003e= 1;\\n            }\\n            pull(L0); pull(R0);\\n        }\\n\\n        int query(int L, int R) {\\n            L += N_; R += N_;\\n            auto result = 0;\\n            push(L); push(R);\\n            while (L \\u003c= R) {\\n                if ((L \\u0026 1) == 1) {\\n                    result = max(result, tree_[L++]);\\n                }\\n                if ((R \\u0026 1) == 0) {\\n                    result = max(result, tree_[R--]);\\n                }\\n                L \\u003e\\u003e= 1; R \\u003e\\u003e= 1;\\n            }\\n            return result;\\n        }\\n\\n    private:\\n        int N_, H_;\\n        vector\\u003cint\\u003e tree_, lazy_;\\n\\n        void apply(int x, int val) {\\n            tree_[x] += val;\\n            if (x \\u003c N_) {\\n                lazy_[x] += val;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        void pull(int x) {\\n            while (x \\u003e 1) {\\n                x \\u003e\\u003e= 1;\\n                tree_[x] = max(tree_[x * 2], tree_[x * 2 + 1]);\\n                if (lazy_[x]) {\\n                    tree_[x] += lazy_[x];\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        void push(int x) {\\n            for (int h = H_; h \\u003e 0; --h) {\\n                int y = x \\u003e\\u003e h;\\n                if (lazy_[y] != 0) {\\n                    apply(y * 2, lazy_[y]);\\n                    apply(y * 2 + 1, lazy_[y]);\\n                    lazy_[y] = 0;\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    };\\n\\n    bool check(const vector\\u003cvector\\u003cint\\u003e\\u003e\\u0026 points, int k, int l) {  // Time: O(nlogn), Space: O(n)\\n        using Event = tuple\\u003cint64_t, int64_t, int64_t, int64_t\\u003e;\\n        vector\\u003cEvent\\u003e intervals;\\n        unordered_set\\u003cint64_t\\u003e y_set;\\n        for (const auto\\u0026 p : points) {\\n            // add [y0, y1] by 1 in [x0, x1+1)\\n            int64_t x0 = int64_t(p[0]) - l, y0 = int64_t(p[1]) - l, x1 = int64_t(p[0]) + l, y1 = int64_t(p[1]) + l;\\n            intervals.emplace_back(x0    , +1, y0, y1);\\n            intervals.emplace_back(x1 + 1, -1, y0, y1);\\n            y_set.emplace(y0);\\n            y_set.emplace(y1);\\n        }\\n        sort(begin(intervals), end(intervals));\\n        vector\\u003cint64_t\\u003e sorted_y(cbegin(y_set), cend(y_set));\\n        sort(begin(sorted_y), end(sorted_y));\\n        unordered_map\\u003cint64_t, int\\u003e y_to_idx;\\n        for (int i = 0; i \\u003c size(sorted_y); ++i) {  // coordinate compression\\n            y_to_idx[sorted_y[i]] = i;\\n        }\\n        SegmentTree st(size(y_to_idx));\\n        for (const auto\\u0026 [_, v, y0, y1] : intervals) {  // line sweep\\n            st.update(y_to_idx[y0], y_to_idx[y1], v);\\n            if (st.query(0, size(y_to_idx) - 1) \\u003e= k) {\\n                return true;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return false;\\n    }\\n};\\n\\n// Time:  O(n^2 * logr), r is the sum of range x size and range y size\\n// Space: O(n)\\n// interview solution\\nclass Solution2 {\\npublic:\\n    int minDayskVariants(vector\\u003cvector\\u003cint\\u003e\\u003e\\u0026 points, int k) {\\n        std::transform(begin(points), end(points), begin(points),\\n                       [](const auto\\u0026 v) {\\n                           return vector\\u003cint\\u003e({v[0] + v[1], v[0] - v[1]});  // rotate\\n                       });\\n        const auto\\u0026 compare_y = [](const vector\\u003cint\\u003e\\u0026 a, const vector\\u003cint\\u003e\\u0026 b) { return a[1] \\u003c b[1]; };\\n        const int min_x = (*min_element(cbegin(points), cend(points)))[0];\\n        const int max_x = (*max_element(cbegin(points), cend(points)))[0];\\n        const int min_y = (*min_element(cbegin(points), cend(points), compare_y))[1];\\n        const int max_y = (*max_element(cbegin(points), cend(points), compare_y))[1];\\n        int64_t left = 0, right = ((int64_t(max_x) - min_x) + (int64_t(max_y) - min_y) + 1) / 2;\\n        while (left \\u003c= right) {\\n            const auto\\u0026 mid = left + (right - left) / 2;\\n            if (check(points, k, mid)) {\\n                right = mid - 1;\\n            } else {\\n                left = mid + 1;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return left;                       \\n    }\\n\\nprivate:\\n    bool check(const vector\\u003cvector\\u003cint\\u003e\\u003e\\u0026 points, int k, int l) {  // Time: O(n^2), Space: O(n)\\n        unordered_map\\u003cint64_t, unordered_map\\u003cint64_t, int\\u003e\\u003e intervals;\\n        unordered_set\\u003cint64_t\\u003e y_set;\\n        for (const auto\\u0026 p : points) {\\n            // add [y0, y1+1) by 1 in [x0, x1+1)\\n            int64_t x0 = int64_t(p[0]) - l, y0 = int64_t(p[1]) - l, x1 = int64_t(p[0]) + l, y1 = int64_t(p[1]) + l;\\n            ++intervals[x0][y0];\\n            --intervals[x0][y1 + 1];\\n            --intervals[x1 + 1][y0];\\n            ++intervals[x1 + 1][y1 + 1];\\n            y_set.emplace(y0);\\n            y_set.emplace(y1 + 1);\\n        }\\n        vector\\u003cint64_t\\u003e sorted_x;\\n        for (const auto\\u0026 [x, _] : intervals) {\\n            sorted_x.emplace_back(x);\\n        }\\n        sort(begin(sorted_x), end(sorted_x));\\n        vector\\u003cint64_t\\u003e sorted_y(cbegin(y_set), cend(y_set));\\n        sort(begin(sorted_y), end(sorted_y));\\n        unordered_map\\u003cint64_t, int\\u003e count;\\n        for (const auto\\u0026 x : sorted_x) {  // line sweep\\n            for (const auto\\u0026 [y, c] : intervals[x]) {\\n                count[y] += c;\\n            }\\n            int cnt = 0;\\n            for (const auto\\u0026 y : sorted_y) {\\n                cnt += count[y];\\n                if (cnt \\u003e= k) {\\n                    return true;\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return false;\\n    }\\n};\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"23:T1752,\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"# Time:  O(nlogn * logr), r is the sum of range x size and range y size\\n# Space: O(n)\\n\\n# Range Maximum Query\\nclass SegmentTree(object):  # 0-based index\\n    def __init__(self, N,\\n                 build_fn=lambda x, y: [y]*(2*x),\\n                 query_fn=lambda x, y: y if x is None else max(x, y),\\n                 update_fn=lambda x, y: y if x is None else x+y,\\n                 default_val=0):\\n        self.N = N\\n        self.H = (N-1).bit_length()\\n        self.query_fn = query_fn\\n        self.update_fn = update_fn\\n        self.default_val = default_val\\n        self.tree = build_fn(N, default_val)\\n        self.lazy = [None]*N\\n\\n    def __apply(self, x, val):\\n        self.tree[x] = self.update_fn(self.tree[x], val)\\n        if x \\u003c self.N:\\n            self.lazy[x] = self.update_fn(self.lazy[x], val)\\n\\n    def update(self, L, R, h):  # Time: O(logN), Space: O(N)\\n        def pull(x):\\n            while x \\u003e 1:\\n                x //= 2\\n                self.tree[x] = self.query_fn(self.tree[x*2], self.tree[x*2+1])\\n                if self.lazy[x] is not None:\\n                    self.tree[x] = self.update_fn(self.tree[x], self.lazy[x])\\n\\n        L += self.N\\n        R += self.N\\n        L0, R0 = L, R\\n        while L \\u003c= R:\\n            if L \\u0026 1:  # is right child\\n                self.__apply(L, h)\\n                L += 1\\n            if R \\u0026 1 == 0:  # is left child\\n                self.__apply(R, h)\\n                R -= 1\\n            L //= 2\\n            R //= 2\\n        pull(L0)\\n        pull(R0)\\n\\n    def query(self, L, R):  # Time: O(logN), Space: O(N)\\n        def push(x):\\n            n = 2**self.H\\n            while n != 1:\\n                y = x // n\\n                if self.lazy[y] is not None:\\n                    self.__apply(y*2, self.lazy[y])\\n                    self.__apply(y*2 + 1, self.lazy[y])\\n                    self.lazy[y] = None\\n                n //= 2\\n\\n        result = None\\n        if L \\u003e R:\\n            return result\\n\\n        L += self.N\\n        R += self.N\\n        push(L)\\n        push(R)\\n        while L \\u003c= R:\\n            if L \\u0026 1:  # is right child\\n                result = self.query_fn(result, self.tree[L])\\n                L += 1\\n            if R \\u0026 1 == 0:  # is left child\\n                result = self.query_fn(result, self.tree[R])\\n                R -= 1\\n            L //= 2\\n            R //= 2\\n        return result\\n    \\n    def __str__(self):\\n        showList = []\\n        for i in xrange(self.N):\\n            showList.append(self.query(i, i))\\n        return \\\",\\\".join(map(str, showList))\\n\\n\\n# competitive programming solution\\nclass Solution(object):\\n    def minDayskVariants(self, points, k):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        :type points: List[List[int]]\\n        :type k: int\\n        :rtype: int\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        def add_rec(rec, intervals):\\n            x0, y0, x1, y1 = rec\\n            # add [y0, y1] by 1 in [x0, x1+1)\\n            intervals.append([[x0,   +1], [y0, y1]])\\n            intervals.append([[x1+1, -1], [y0, y1]])\\n\\n        def check(points, k, l):  # Time: O(nlogn), Space: O(n)\\n            intervals = []\\n            y_set = set()\\n            for x, y in points:\\n                add_rec([x-l, y-l, x+l, y+l], intervals)\\n                y_set.add(y-l)\\n                y_set.add(y+l)\\n            intervals.sort()\\n            y_to_idx = {y:i for i, y in enumerate(sorted(y_set))}  # coordinate compression\\n            st = SegmentTree(len(y_to_idx))\\n            for [_, v], [y0, y1] in intervals:  # line sweep\\n                st.update(y_to_idx[y0], y_to_idx[y1], v)\\n                if st.query(0, len(y_to_idx)-1) \\u003e= k:\\n                    return True\\n            return False\\n                \\n        points = [[x+y, x-y] for x, y in points]  # rotate\\n        min_x = min(points)[0]\\n        max_x = max(points)[0]\\n        min_y = min(points, key=lambda x: x[1])[1]\\n        max_y = max(points, key=lambda x: x[1])[1]\\n        left, right = 0, ((max_x-min_x)+(max_y-min_y)+1)//2\\n        while left \\u003c= right:\\n            mid = left + (right-left)//2\\n            if check(points, k, mid):\\n                right = mid-1\\n            else:\\n                left = mid+1\\n        return left\\n\\n\\n# Time:  O(n^2 * logr), r is the sum of range x size and range y size\\n# Space: O(n)\\nimport collections\\n\\n\\n# interview solution\\nclass Solution2(object):\\n    def minDayskVariants(self, points, k):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        :type points: List[List[int]]\\n        :type k: int\\n        :rtype: int\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        def add_rec(rec, intervals):\\n            x0, y0, x1, y1 = rec\\n            # add [y0, y1+1) by 1 in [x0, x1+1)\\n            intervals[x0][y0] += 1\\n            intervals[x0][y1+1] -= 1\\n            intervals[x1+1][y0] -= 1\\n            intervals[x1+1][y1+1] += 1\\n\\n        def check(points, k, l):  # Time: O(n^2), Space: O(n)\\n            intervals = collections.defaultdict(lambda:collections.defaultdict(int))\\n            y_set = set()\\n            for x, y in points:\\n                add_rec([x-l, y-l, x+l, y+l], intervals)\\n                y_set.add(y-l)\\n                y_set.add(y+l+1)\\n            sorted_y = sorted(y_set)\\n            sorted_x = sorted(intervals.iterkeys())\\n            count = collections.Counter()\\n            for x in sorted_x:  # line sweep\\n                for y, c in intervals[x].iteritems():\\n                    count[y] += c\\n                cnt = 0\\n                for y in sorted_y:\\n                    cnt += count[y]\\n                    if cnt \\u003e= k:\\n                        return True\\n            return False\\n                \\n        points = [[x+y, x-y] for x, y in points]  # rotate\\n        min_x = min(points)[0]\\n        max_x = max(points)[0]\\n        min_y = min(points, key=lambda x: x[1])[1]\\n        max_y = max(points, key=lambda x: x[1])[1]\\n        left, right = 0, ((max_x-min_x)+(max_y-min_y)+1)//2\\n        while left \\u003c= right:\\n            mid = left + (right-left)//2\\n            if check(points, k, mid):\\n                right = mid-1\\n            else:\\n                left = mid+1\\n        return left\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"1f:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-6 grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_280px] gap-10\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"article\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"header\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"space-y-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm text-muted-foreground tabular-nums\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"#\\\",1956]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-hard/15 text-hard\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Hard\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-muted text-muted-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Premium on LC\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"~\\\",50,\\\" min\\\"]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h1\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Minimum Time For K Virus Variants to Spread\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Time \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"strong\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"O(nlogn * logr)\\\"}],\\\" · \\\",\\\"Space \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"strong\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"O(n)\\\"}],\\\" · \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"a\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-time-for-k-virus-variants-to-spread/\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"_blank\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-primary underline-offset-2 hover:underline\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Official statement on LeetCode\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex flex-wrap gap-2\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",\\\"geometry\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/topics/geometry\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-primary/15 text-primary\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"geometry\\\"}]}]],[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",\\\"binary-search\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/patterns/binary-search\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"binary search\\\"}]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",\\\"segment-tree\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/patterns/segment-tree\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"segment tree\\\"}]}]],[]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex flex-wrap gap-2 pt-1\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L20\\\",null,{\\\"slug\\\":\\\"minimum-time-for-k-virus-variants-to-spread\\\"}],[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",\\\"cpp\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/problems/minimum-time-for-k-virus-variants-to-spread/cpp\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm text-primary hover:underline\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"cpp\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",\\\"python\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/problems/minimum-time-for-k-virus-variants-to-spread/python\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm text-primary hover:underline\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"python\\\"}]]]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-10\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"solutions\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xl font-bold mb-3\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Solutions\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L21\\\",null,{\\\"solutions\\\":{\\\"cpp\\\":{\\\"language\\\":\\\"C++\\\",\\\"languageSlug\\\":\\\"cpp\\\",\\\"filename\\\":\\\"minimum-time-for-k-virus-variants-to-spread.cpp\\\",\\\"code\\\":\\\"$22\\\",\\\"sourcePath\\\":\\\"C++/minimum-time-for-k-virus-variants-to-spread.cpp\\\"},\\\"python\\\":{\\\"language\\\":\\\"Python\\\",\\\"languageSlug\\\":\\\"python\\\",\\\"filename\\\":\\\"minimum-time-for-k-virus-variants-to-spread.py\\\",\\\"code\\\":\\\"$23\\\",\\\"sourcePath\\\":\\\"Python/minimum-time-for-k-virus-variants-to-spread.py\\\"}}}]]}],[\\\"$L24\\\",\\\"$L25\\\",\\\"$L26\\\",\\\"$L27\\\",\\\"$L28\\\",\\\"$L29\\\",\\\"$L2a\\\",\\\"$L2b\\\",\\\"$L2c\\\",\\\"$L2d\\\"],\\\"$L2e\\\",\\\"$L2f\\\",\\\"$L30\\\",\\\"$L31\\\",\\\"$L32\\\",\\\"$L33\\\"]}],\\\"$L34\\\"]}]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"3c:I[203221,[\\\"/_next/static/chunks/2fvm6eoqeukxu.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/1ntn7efqc-iiw.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0plpm2axnqe9k.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/259rkrk9l2f9c.js\\\"],\\\"ConfidenceTracker\\\"]\\n35:T443,\\u003ch2\\u003eWhat is Minimum Time For K Virus Variants to Spread?\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eMinimum Time For K Virus Variants to Spread\\u003c/strong\\u003e (LeetCode #1956) is a \\u003cstrong\\u003eHard\\u003c/strong\\u003e problem that primarily trains \\u003cstrong\\u003egeometry\\u003c/strong\\u003e.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eHow to think about it\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003col\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eRestate the goal\\u003c/strong\\u003e in your own words before coding.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eWork a \\u003cstrong\\u003etiny example\\u003c/strong\\u003e by hand so the invariant becomes obvious.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eIdentify the \\u003cstrong\\u003epattern\\u003c/strong\\u003e — this problem aligns with \\u003cstrong\\u003ebinary search and segment tree\\u003c/strong\\u003e.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eOnly then translate the idea into code.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ol\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eWhy this problem matters\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eHard problems force you to combine patterns and prove complexity carefully — interview gold.\\nOfficial solution notes mention: Geometry, Binary Search, Line Sweep, Segment Tree.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cblockquote\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eAlgoForge explanations are original teaching notes. Always open the \\u003ca href=\\\"https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-time-for-k-virus-variants-to-spread/\\\"\\u003eofficial problem statement on LeetCode\\u003c/a\\u003e for constraints and examples.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003c/blockquote\\u003e\\n24:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",\\\"beginner\\\",{\\\"id\\\":\\\"beginner\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xl font-bold\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Beginner Explanation\\\"}],false]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"prose-af\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"$35\\\"}}]]}]\\n36:T4e7,\\u003ch2\\u003eInterview approach for Minimum Time For K Virus Variants to Spread\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eOpening (30–60 seconds)\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eClarify inputs/outputs and edge cases (empty input, single element, duplicates, overflow).\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eState a \\u003cstrong\\u003ebrute force\\u003c/strong\\u003e so the interviewer knows you can solve it naively.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003ePropose the \\u003cstrong\\u003eoptimal direction\\u003c/strong\\u003e tied to \\u003cstrong\\u003ebinary search and segment tree\\u003c/strong\\u003e.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eCore solution narrative\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003col\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eDefine the \\u003cstrong\\u003estate\\u003c/strong\\u003e you track (pointers, DP cell, set membership, stack top, etc.).\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eExplain the \\u003cstrong\\u003etransition\\u003c/strong\\u003e when you process the next element.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eCall out \\u003cstrong\\u003etime\\u003c/strong\\u003e (O(nlogn * logr)) and \\u003cstrong\\u003espace\\u003c/strong\\u003e (O(n)) before coding.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eCode cleanly; narrate variable names.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ol\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eWhat interviewers listen for\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eCorrectness on edge cases\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eComplexity honesty\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\